<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="180" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,222,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tolkanitz" authorityYear="2003" box="[330,501,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Exochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="certus">
<emphasis box="[330,501,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Exochus certus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the combination of the following characters: face not strongly swollen, face in upper half, clypeus laterally and malar space partly yellow; frons black; yellow marks opposite to lateral ocelli not elongated; clypeus with apical margin straight; occipital carina absent dorsally; meso- and metasoma black; propodeum with area superomedia partly opened, costulae distinct, area dentipara only partly pubescent; fore wing with vein 
<emphasis box="[439,489,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">cu-a</emphasis>
strongly distad of 
<emphasis box="[698,771,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
by about 0.4 of own length; third laterotergite more-or-less rounded from the proximal end; legs: coxae black basally, yellow apically, hind trochanters black; fore and mid tibiae fuscous basally and apically, whitish centrally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1220,474,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,574]" box="[199,1220,474,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,474,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently known only from the Kunashir Island of 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1007,475,501]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tolkanitz, V. I." box="[1021,1209,475,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" pagination="339 - 358" refId="ref5020" refString="Tolkanitz, V. I. (2007 a) Ichneumon flies of the genus Exochus Gravenhorst (Hymenoptera: Ichneumonidae: Metopiinae) of the fauna of Palaearctic region. Russian Entomological Journal, 16 (3), 339 - 358." type="journal article" year="2007">Tolkanitz 2007a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[475,653,511,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" refId="ref5125" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2016) World Ichneumonoidea 2015. Taxonomy, Biology, Morphology and Distribution. Nepean, Ontario. [program]" type="book" year="2016">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[514,570,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
the 
<typeStatus box="[702,800,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species is deposited at the Zoological Institute of RAS, but actually it is in 
<collectingRegion box="[435,492,547,573]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Kyiv</collectingRegion>
, which is metioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Zerova, M. D. &amp; Tolkanitz, V. I. &amp; Kotenko, A. G. &amp; Seryogina, L. Y. &amp; Diakontshuk, L. A. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Gumovsky, O. V. &amp; Fursov, V. N. &amp; Simutnik, S. A. &amp; Narolsky, N. B. &amp; Stetsenko, T. I." box="[744,972,547,574]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref5164" refString="Zerova, M. D., Tolkanitz, V. I., Kotenko, A. G., Seryogina, L. Y., Diakontshuk, L. A., Melika, G., Gumovsky, O. V., Fursov, V. N., Simutnik, S. A., Narolsky, N. B. &amp; Stetsenko, T. I. (2006) The Types of Ichneumonoidea, Cynipoidea and Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera, Apocrita) Deposited in the Collection of the Schmalhausen Institute of Zoology of National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine. Zoodiversity, Supplement 20, 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="2006">
Zerova 
<emphasis box="[831,887,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
